description:
Here, we discover the International Hub of Reform in Geneva, Switzerland. Geneva became a city of refuge for many of the hunted reformers across Western Europe. Coupled with that, almost everyone who made a significant impact in the 16th century Reformation passed through Geneva. It became a centre of networking and study, known for its theological pedigree and missionary training, with John Calvin integral to much of the work there. The Reformers Wall commemorates the role that the city played in the Protestant Reformation. 

To find out more about the reformation hub in Geneva, visit our website to read our extended article.
